I too agree that learnability is very critical attribute to any interface.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="13" relname="span"> What sometimes 
happen is that interfaces are designed so badly that users just simply don&apos;t use some of 
the features of the system.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="2" relname="elaboration"> They tend to learn just enough to get by and forget about the 
complex stuff.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="2" relname="nonvolitional-result"> This obviously can lead to efficientcy problems.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="12" relname="span"> I myself have done this.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="11" relname="span"> I 
